member.name: M:Xignite.Sdk.Api.XigniteAnalysts.GetResearchField(System.String,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteAnalysts.IdentifierTypes,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteAnalysts.AnalystFieldTypes)
member.summary: Returns an AnalystsResearchField object for a single identifier. This operation lets you get a particular piece of data for a security.
member.param: The identifier for the company or security as determined by the IdentifierType parameter. Examples: MSFT

The identifier type. Valid values are:
CIK: Identifier is the Central Index Key for the companies, which is a number used on SEC systems to identify companies and other registered entities.
Use the LookupCIK operation to find the CIK for a company.
CUSIP: Identifier is the CUSIP for the companies.
CUSIPs are unique security identifiers managed by The CUSIP Service Bureau.
Symbol: Identifier is the symbol for the company, e.g. MSFT, DELL, or ORCL.
Supports multiple symbologies, check here for details.
ISIN: Identifier is the ISIN 12-character alpha numeric code identifying a security.
Valoren: Identifier is the Valoren number assigned to a financial instrument. Examples: Symbol

The type of analyst field you want. There are 5 analyst sets to the left of the underscore which are narrowed down with a more specific type of data you want returned to the right.
The 5 field sets are:
Security
CurrentSalesConsensus
CurrentSalesConsensusChange
SummaryCurrentStatistics
SummaryCurrentStatisticsChange Examples: Security_Ticker

summary.p: The offset or difference, in hours, from the local exchange time to UTC. For example, the offset is -5 for Eastern Standard Time. This offset value is applicable to the Last price time (the Time output parameter) returned.
This property can be used to convert the Time to UTC:

ul.li: Formula: Time - UTCOffset = UTC
Example: Time=3:00 PM and UTCOffset=-5 results in UTC=8:00 PM.

member.name: M:Xignite.Sdk.Api.XigniteBATSRealTime.GetRealQuoteByIdentifier(System.String,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteBATSRealTime.IdentifierTypes)
member.summary: Returns a real-time quote for a security. One of various identifier types can be used.
member.param: The identifier for the security as determined by the IdentifierType parameter. Examples: 0000789019

The identifier type. Valid values are:
CIK: Identifier is the Central Index Key assigned to a security's issuing company, which is a number used on SEC systems to identify companies and other registered entities.
CUSIP: Identifier is the number identifying all stock and registered bonds, using the Committee on Uniform Securities Identification Procedures (CUSIP).
CUSIPs are unique security identifiers managed by The CUSIP Service Bureau.
Symbol: Identifier is the ticker symbol for the security, e.g. MSFT.
ISIN: Identifier is the 12-character alpha-numeric International Securities Identification Number (ISO 6166 ISIN) assigned to a security.
Valoren: Identifier is the Valoren number assigned to a financial instrument. Examples: CIK

member.name: M:Xignite.Sdk.Api.XigniteBATSRealTime.GetBar(System.String,System.String,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteBATSRealTime.TickPrecisions,System.Int32)
member.summary: Returns a single summarized quote bar for a specific time during the trading day.
member.param: The symbol for the security. Examples: MSFT
The ending time for the summarized trade bar. The time may be entered in 12-hr or 24-hr format: HH:MM AM/PM or HH:MM Examples: 10:00 AM

The precision unit to apply to the summarized quote bars. Choose:
Seconds to summarize quotes by the number of seconds specified by Periods.
Minutes to summarize quotes by the number of minutes specified by Periods.
Hours to summarize quotes by the number of hours specified by Periods.
For instance, Precision=Minutes and Period=15 will return one quote bar every fifteen minutes, including the open, high, low and close within that fifteen minute period. Examples: Minutes

Used in combination with Precision to define the number of units to apply to summarized quote bars. For instance, Precision=Minutes and Period=15 will return one summarized quote bar every fifteen minutes. Examples: 15

member.name: M:Xignite.Sdk.Api.XigniteCompensation.GetOfficers(System.String,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteCompensation.IdentifierTypes)
member.summary: Returns all officers for a company (including those who are no longer active).
member.param: The identifier for the company or security as determined by the IdentifierType parameter. Examples: MSFT

The identifier type. Valid values are:
CIK: Identifier is the Central Index Key for the companies, which is a number used on SEC systems to identify companies and other registered entities.
Use the LookupCIK operation to find the CIK for a company.
CUSIP: Identifier is the CUSIP for the companies.
CUSIPs are unique security identifiers managed by The CUSIP Service Bureau.
Symbol: Identifier is the symbol for the company, e.g. MSFT, DELL, or ORCL.
Supports multiple symbologies, check here for details.
ISIN: Identifier is the ISIN 12-character alpha numeric code identifying a security.
Valoren: Identifier is the Valoren number assigned to a financial instrument. Examples: Symbol

CUSIPs are unique security identifiers managed by The CUSIP Service Bureau.
Symbol: Identifier is the symbol for the company, e.g. MSFT, DELL, or ORCL.

ISIN: Identifier is the ISIN 12-character alpha numeric code identifying a security.
Valoren: Identifier is the Valoren number assigned to a financial instrument. Examples: Symbol

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteEarningsCalendar.Announcement.DateType
member.summary:
The confirmation status of the next earnings date. Valid types are:
Verified: indicates that this is a Verified date, gathered through the WSH data collection process and confirmed by the company . If you republish this data, WSH strongly recommends that these dates be referred to as 'Verified'.
Tentative: indicates that the date was gathered from the company by the WSH data collection process but it is still considered Tentative by the company, or estimated by one of our data analysts. If you republish this data, WSH strongly recommends that these dates be referred to as 'Unconfirmed'.
Inferred: indicates that the date is forecasted (or Inferred) using WSH proprietary algorithm. If you re-publish this data, WSH strongly recommends that these dates be referred to as 'Unconfirmed'.

member.name: M:Xignite.Sdk.Api.XigniteEdgar.SearchFilings(System.String,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteEdgar.IdentifierTypes,System.String,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteEdgar.OwnershipFormTypes,System.String,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteEdgar.OutputTypes)
member.summary: Search the EDGAR database for company filings, including real-time filings. Returns more information than the QueryFilings operation but is slower. Company filings are available from 1993 through today. The operation returns two important values: TextFileUrl and HtmlFileUrl. These two URLs point to the files that list the contents of the filing. TextFileUrl points to a file that actually provides all the content of the filing in text format. HtmlFileUrl points to a file that provides a list of URLs to the file(s) that make up the filing. You can then use the GetFilingDetails operation to retrieve additional information about this file and the list of documents included together with their URL.
member.param: The identifier for the company as determined by the IdentifierType parameter. Examples: MSFT

The identifier type. Valid values are:
CIK: Identifier is the SEC Central Index Key for the company.
Use the LookupCIK operation to find the CIK for a company.
CUSIP: Identifier is the CUSIP for the company.
CUSIPS are unique security identifiers managed by The CUSIP Service Bureau .
Symbol: Identifier is the symbol for the company, e.g. MSFT, DELL, or ORCL.
Supports multiple Symbologies, check here for details.
ISIN: Identifier is the ISIN 12-character alpha numeric code identifying a security.
Valoren: Identifier is the Valoren number assigned to a Swiss financial instrument. Examples: Symbol
The form for which to retrieve the recent filings. This is a free-form text field, so entering 10 will retrieve all forms starting with 10, i.e., 10, 10-K, 10-K/A, 10-Q... Examples: 10
Choose whether Forms 3, 4 and 5 should be included or excluded from the search, or whether the search should be limited to these forms. Examples: Include
Enter a date to limit results to filings made before this date. Invalid dates (format MM/DD/YYY) are ignored. Examples: 01/05/2007
Choose how many matching records to return. Note that the more records, the slower the query. Examples: Top80Matches

member.summary: List recent SEC filings (today to up to five days ago) for the most popular SEC forms (10-K, 10-Q...). This includes real-time filings for the current day. Note that thousands of new filings are typically made with the SEC every single working day. The operation returns two important values: TextFileUrl and HtmlFileUrl. These two URLs point to the files that list the contents of the filing. TextFileUrl points to a file that actually provides all the content of the filing in text format. HtmlFileUrl points to a file that provides a list of URLs to the file(s) that make up the filing. You can then use the GetFilingDetails operation to retrieve additional information about this file and the list of documents included together with their URL.
member.param: The day for which to retrieve the recent filings. Examples: Today
The form for which to retrieve the recent filings. Use All to return all filings. Examples: Form10K

member.name: M:Xignite.Sdk.Api.XigniteEdgar.GetFilingDetails(System.String)
member.summary: Retrieves a specific HTML filing and lists the documents it contains. This operation returns the complete Header information for the file. It also returns an array of Documents, each pointing to a specific file included in the filing.Note that you can retrieve this file directly by using the HtmlFileUrl value. Use the FileSize attribute to verify the size of the file. Large files can be slow to retrieve.
member.param:
The url for the file. This parameter must match the HtmlFileUrl value returned by the SearchFilings, GetLastFilings, and GetRecentFilings operations. You can omit the case-sensitive http://www.sec.gov/ Archives/edgar/data/ prefix. Examples: 789019/000119312503045632/000

.htm

member.name: M:Xignite.Sdk.Api.XigniteEstimates.GetResearchField(System.String,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteEstimates.IdentifierTypes,Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteEstimates.EstimateFieldTypes)
member.summary: Returns an EstimatesResearchField object for a single identifier. This operation lets you get a particular piece of data for a security.
member.param: The identifier for the company as determined by the IdentifierType parameter. Examples: MSFT

The identifier type. Valid values are:
CIK: Identifier is the SEC Central Index Key for the company.
Use the LookupCIK operation to find the CIK for a company.
CUSIP: Identifier is the CUSIP for the company.
CUSIPS are unique security identifiers managed by The CUSIP Service Bureau.
Symbol: Identifier is the symbol for the company, e.g. MSFT, DELL, or ORCL.
Supports multiple Symbologies, check here for details.
Valoren: Identifier is the Valoren number assigned to a Swiss financial instrument.
ISIN: Identifier is the ISIN 12-character alpha numeric code identifying a security. Examples: Symbol

The type of estimate field you want. There are 9 estimate sets to the left of the underscore which are narrowed down with a more specific piece of data you want returned to the right.
The 9 field sets are:
Security
EarningsEstimates
EarningsEstimatesConsensusTrend
EarningsSurprise
EPSGrowthRates
AnalystRecommendations
AnalystRecommendationsAndHistogram
SectorAnalysis
EPSEstimatesAndRcommendations Examples: Security_Ticker

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown
member.summary: for most companies this includes taxes other than income taxes particularly excise taxes, which the company does not actually pay, but only collects on behalf of the government (common for Tobacco, Liquor, Firearm industry) and other adjustments which have been 'netted' out of revenue. For financial companies reporting in Industrial Template, all expenses other than interest expense and income taxes are included in Adjustments to Revenue.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown.ProvisionForLoanLosses
member.summary: It is an estimate of future loan losses based on current and past figures. Usually it is an evaluation of risk, collectability, and the value of collateral in the loan portfolio.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown.SalariesAndEmployeeBenefits
member.summary: Salaries and employee benefits

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown.NetOccupancyExpense
member.summary: Net Occupancy Expense includes property, plant, equipment, utilities and rent expense.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown.PromotionAndAdvertising
member.summary: Includes any marketing and advertising costs.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown.PropertyLiabilityInsuranceClaims
member.summary: It includes any amounts the company had to pay on property, life, title and liability insurance claims.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown.AmortizationOfDeferredPolicyAcquisitionCosts
member.summary: Amortization of deferred policy acquisition costs, a field common to insurance companies

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown.CurrentAndFutureBenefits
member.summary: It is an amount or fund that is set aside to cover claim obligations for the year, a field common to insurance companies.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown.TotalNonInterestExpense
member.summary: Equals Salaries and Employee Benefits + Net Occupancy Expense + Promotion and Advertising Expense + Property and Liability Insurance Claims + Policy Acquisition Costs + Amortization of Deferred Policy Acquisition Costs + Current and Future Benefits + Other Non-Interest Expense

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown.PremiumTaxOrCredit
member.summary: Includes federal government taxes on premiums earned from issuing insurance policies, a field common to insurance companies.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFlowStatement.CashAtEndOfPeriod
member.summary: The cash and equivalents balance at the end of the accounting period, as indicated on the Cash Flow statement for the reporting period. It is equal to the Beginning Cash and Equivalents, plus the Net Change in Cash and Equivalents.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFlowStatement.EffectofExchangeRateChanges
member.summary: includes any gains/losses from the translation from foreign to U.S. dollars.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities
member.summary: Instance of CashFromFinancingActivities

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.IssuanceOfDebt
member.summary: Includes all items that involve proceeds from current and long-term debt issued to clients. Typical Accounts: Proceeds from long-term and short-term borrowing; Additional long-term, short-term borrowing; Increase in short-term loan payable; Sale of receivables

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.IssuanceOfCapitalStock
member.summary: Includes items that involve the issuance of common and preferred stock, and the sale of treasury stock. Typical Accounts: sale of common/treasury stock, sale of convertibles, issued preferred stock, increase/decrease in commercial paper, options to convert exercised, disposition of shares from company treasury, and issue stock under stock option plan for employees

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.IssuanceOfCapitalStockBreakdown
member.summary: Instance of IssuanceOfCapitalStockBreakdown. Note: Usually Financial services companies provide breakdown of some items defined in the output.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.RepaymentOfDebt
member.summary: Includes the payments of long term obligations (over one year).

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.RepurchaseOfCapitalStock
member.summary: Includes anything that involves the repurchase of common and preferred stock for the treasury. Typical Accounts: Treasury stock acquired/purchased; Repurchase company shares for treasury; Return of capital to shareholders; Redemption of preferred stock/common stock

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.PurchaseOfTreasuryStock
member.summary: Includes anything that involves the repurchase of common and preferred stock for the treasury.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.CashDividendsPaid
member.summary: Includes cash payments of common and preferred dividends to the shareholders. Preferred dividends are the amount required for the current year only and not for any amount in prior years.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.NetOtherFinancingCharges
member.summary: Includes any financing item that is not assigned to: Debt, Capital Stock, Payment of Cash Dividends. Typical Accounts: Realization (repayment) of purchases tax benefit; Cash payment on outstanding interest rate swaps; Repurchase of receivables from banks; Proceeds from sale and leaseback of assets; Addition to minority interest; Sale of affiliated preferred stock

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.CashFromDiscontinuedFinancingActivities
member.summary: Earnings from operations sold or discontinued over the designated time period.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromFinancingActivities.NetCashFromFinancingActivities
member.summary: Equals Issuance of Debt + Issuance of Capital Stock + Repayment of Long-Term Debt + Repurchase Capital Stock + Payment of Cash Dividends + Other Financing Changes, Net.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities
member.summary: Instance of CashFromInvestingActivities

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.SaleOfPropertyPlantAndEquipment
member.summary: includes the amount received from selling any fixed assets such as property, plant and equipment. Usually this section also includes any retirement of equipment. Typical Accounts: Sale of business segments; Sale of credit and receivables; Property disposition; Proceeds from sale or disposition of business or investment; Decrease in excess of purchase price over acquired net assets; Abandoned project (expenditures) credit; Allowances for other funds during construction

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.SaleOfLongTermInvestments
member.summary: Profits received from selling Long Term Marketable securities.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.SaleOfShortTermInvestments
member.summary: includes profit received from selling short term marketable securities. Typical Accounts: Proceeds from short-term investments; Investment in leveraged leases; Treasury bills; Certificates of deposit; Banker's acceptances; Money market investments; Commercial paper; Eurodollars; Repurchase Agreements (RPs); Collateral investments; Temporary investments

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.Acquisitions
member.summary: Increase in property, plant and equipment as a result of acquisitions. To be distinguished from the purchase of property, plant and equipment.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.PurchaseOfLongTermInvestments
member.summary: All purchases of long term investments

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.PurchaseOfShortTermInvestments
member.summary: includes all purchases of short-term investment items. Typical Accounts: Purchase short-term investments; Investment in common stock equity; Marketable equity securities and other; Purchase treasury bills; Purchase certificates of deposit; Treasury Bills; Trading account securities; Money Market investments; Commercial paper; Eurodollars; Repurchase Agreements (RPs); Interest Bearing Deposit Accounts; Demand deposit (interest bearing);Interest bearing checking account; Savings account; Deposit in foreign offices; Money market certificates and deposit accounts

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.PurchaseOfInvestmentSecurities
member.summary: Also known as Purchase of Short-Term Investments, this field includes all purchases of short-term investment items..

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.OtherInvestingChangesNet
member.summary: includes any items that are not assigned to purchases, selling of fixed assets, or investments. Typical Accounts: Investment in subsidiary; Investment in affiliated companies; Proceeds from life insurance; Purchases of other assets; Intangible assets; Acquisitions & development of software; Equipment under operating leases; Proceeds from sale of discontinued operations; Reduction in investment deposits; Decrease in invest-bearing balance with banks; Payment to increase tax basis of acquired company assets

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.CashFromDiscontinuedInvestingActivities
member.summary: Earnings from operations sold or discontinued over the designated time period.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromInvestingActivities.NetCashFromInvestingActivities
member.summary: Equals Sale Property, Plant, Equipment + Sale Short-Term Investments + Purchase Property, Plant, Equipment + Purchase Short-Term Debt + Other Investing Changes

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities
member.summary: Instance of CashFromOperatingActivities

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.DepreciationExpenses
member.summary: The apportionment of cost over an operational asset's useful life. This field is to be loaded as reported in the Operating Activities section of the Cash Flow Statement. Include any variation where Depreciation is the first account listed in the line item

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.AmortizationExpenses
member.summary: The systematic and rational apportionment of the acquisition cost of intangible operational assets to future periods in which the benefits contribute to revenue. This field is to include Amortization and any variation where Amortization is the first account listed in the line item, excluding Amortization of Intangibles.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.AmortizationOfIntangiblesExpenses
member.summary: The apportionment of expenses dealing strictly with intangible assets.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.DeferredIncomeTaxes
member.summary: the estimated future tax obligations which usually arise when different depreciation methods are used for financial statements and tax purposes. It is also an add-back to the Statement of Cash Flows. Deferred Income Taxes includes accumulated tax deferrals due to accelerated depreciation and investment credit. Typical Accounts: Federal income tax; State and local income tax; Income tax credit; Investment tax credits; Tax benefits

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.OperatingGainsOrLosses
member.summary: includes any adjustments that involve the actual operations of the company. These items actually effect the income of the company. Typical Accounts: Provision for returns & allowances; provision for credit losses; provision for bad debt Provision for losses on Trade & Other Accounts Receivable; Compensatory stock expense; Realized Gains & Losses; Foreign currency translation loss/gain; Net security loss/gain; Estimated restructuring loss; Gain loss on early debt extinguishment; Gain/loss on sale and leaseback; Gain/loss on settlement of pension obligation

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.ExtraordinaryGainsOrLosses
member.summary: includes income incurred from extraordinary events and transactions that are both infrequent and unusual. Examples: 1. Act of God. 2. Property taken by a foreign country. 3. A new law/regulation. Typical Accounts: Extraordinary Items; Extraordinary Credit

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.IncreaseOrDecreaseInReceivables
member.summary: the increase or decrease between periods of the Receivables. Receivables are amounts due to be paid to the company from clients and other. Typical Accounts: Accounts receivable; Notes receivable; Trade receivable; Other receivable; Accrued receivables; Unbilled costs and estimated earnings on contract in progress; Money due from sales of debentures; Unbilled shipments; Amounts due from officers and employees; Commercial paper listed by subsidiaries to parent company; Store property covered by investors commitments to purchase

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.IncreaseOrDecreaseInInventories
member.summary: the increase or decrease between periods of the Inventories. Inventories represent merchandise bought for resale and supplies and raw materials purchased for use in revenue producing operations.Typical Accounts:Inventories; Materials and supplies; Raw Materials; Work in process; Finished goods; Merchandise; Merchandise in transit; U.S. Government contract billings and expensed contracts; Deposits/advances on material purchases; Work iprocess and advances to subcontractors (net of progress payments); Advance manufacturing costs; Revenue stamps; Unbilled costs on U.S. Government contracts; Advances to planters; Fuel, oil and gas (utilities); Advances to other producers (motion picture companies); Storage charges (distilleries); Film costs net of accumulated depreciation; Program broadcast rights; Tires and trucking supplies for transportation companies; Bullion for gold and silver mining companies

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.IncreaseOrDecreaseInOtherCurrentAssets
member.summary: the increase or decrease between periods of the Other Current Assets. Other Current Assets includes all other current assets that are not assigned to accounts receivable and inventories. This category typically includes prepayments, deferred charges, and amounts (other than trade accounts) due from parents and subsidiaries. Typical Accounts: Other current assets; Current deferred taxes; Current expenses applicable to future operations; Cash surrender value of life insurance

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.IncreaseOrDecreaseInPayables
member.summary: the increase or decrease between periods of the Payables

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.IncreaseOrDecreaseInOtherCurrentLiabilities
member.summary: the increase or decrease between periods of the Other Current Assets. Other Current Liabilities includes all other current liabilities that do not fit into short-term debt.Typical Accounts:Accrued taxes; Current dividends payable; Current taxes payable; Current accrued liabilities; Advance ticket sales (airlines); Accrued compensation; Accrued expense; Other current liabilities; Increase in self insurance; Interest payable Payroll payable; Commission payable; Deferred income tax; Unearned rent/revenue; Deferred revenue; Unearned premiums; Policyholder funds; Franchise deposits; Security sold under agreement to repurchase; Insurance and annuity reserves; Travelers' checks outstanding; Checks outstanding; Deferred research revenue; Policy claims and reserves; Payment service obligations; Advances and billing in excess of related costs.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.IncreaseOrDecreaseInOtherWorkingCapital
member.summary: the increase or decrease between periods of the Working Capital. Working Capital is the amount left to the company to finance operations and expansion after current liabilities have been covered.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.OtherNonCashItems
member.summary: includes all items that are not considered non-current assets, long-term debt, and liabilities. Includes any other items that are not assigned to depreciation & amortization, deferred income taxes, operating gains/losses, extraordinary gains/losses, or working capital.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.OtherNonCashItemsBreakdown
member.summary: Breakdown of other Non-Cash items.Note: Usually Financial services companies provide breakdown of some items defined in the output.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.NetCashFromContinuingOperations
member.summary: Depreciation & Amortization + Deferred Income Taxes + Operating Gains/Losses + Extraordinary Gains/Losses + Accounts Receivable + Inventories + Other Current Assets + Accounts Payable + Other Current Liabilities + Other Changes in Working Capital + Other Non-Cash Items.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.NetCashFromDiscontinuedOperations
member.summary: income from operations sold or discontinued during the accounting period. This is not an extraordinary gain/loss

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CashFromOperatingActivities.NetCashFromOperatingActivities
member.summary: Net Cash Continuing Operations + Net Cash Discontinuing Operations

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios
member.summary: Each instance represents common ratios for the company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.ClosePERatio
member.summary: The fiscal year closing price divided by the fiscal year earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items).

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.HighPERatio
member.summary: The fiscal year high price divided by the fiscal year earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items)

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.LowPERatio
member.summary: The fiscal year low price divided by the fiscal year earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items)

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.GrossProfitMargin
member.summary: The fiscal year revenues minus fiscal year cost of goods sold divided by the revenues, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.PreTaxProfitMargin
member.summary: The fiscal year pre-tax earnings from Continuing Operations (not including discontinued extraordinary items) divided by the fiscal year revenues, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.PostTaxProfitMargin
member.summary: The fiscal year post-tax earnings from Continuing Operations (not including discontinued or extraordinary items) divided by the fiscal year Revenues, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.NetProfitMargin
member.summary: The fiscal year net income from Continuing Operations and Discontinued Operations divided by the fiscal year revenues, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.InterestCoverageFromContinuingOperations
member.summary: "The fiscal year Earnings from Continuing Operations(before interest and taxes) divided by the Interest Expense.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.InterestAsPercentageOfInvestedCapital
member.summary: The fiscal year interest expense divided by invested capital, expressed as a percentage

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.EffectiveTaxRate
member.summary: The percentage of the company's pre-tax earnings paid in taxes in the form of a percentage. Fiscal year income taxes paid divided by the fiscal year Pre-Tax Earnings.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CommonRatios.IncomePerEmployee
member.summary: The fiscal year net income from total operations divided by the fiscal year employee number.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentAssets.Inventories

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentAssets.PrepaidExpenses

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentAssets.CurrentDeferredIncomeTaxes

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentAssets.OtherCurrentAssets
member.summary: Other Current Assets: includes prepayments, deferred charges, and amounts (other than trade accounts) due from parents and subsidiaries. Also includes any other current assets that are not assigned to cash and cash equivalents, receivables, or inventories.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentAssets.TotalCurrentAssets
member.summary: Total Current Assets: equals cash and equivalents + receivables + inventories + other current assets. Total current assets is the total amount of assets considered to be convertible into cash within a relatively short period of time, usually a year.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentLiabilities.AccountsPayable
member.summary: Accounts Payable: money owed (payable) to suppliers for goods or services purchased on credit; these must be paid within 12 months.

member.summary: represents the amount of borrowings (principal and interest) that must be paid in the near future (usually one year).

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentLiabilities.AccruedExpenses
member.summary: Expenses incurred during the accounting period, but not required to be paid until a late date.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentLiabilities.AccruedLiabilities
member.summary: The catch-all field for amounts owed but not yet paid on a responsibility or requirement.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentLiabilities.DeferredRevenues
member.summary: Unearned revenues or revenues collected in advance.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentLiabilities.CurrentDeferredIncomeTaxLiabilities
member.summary: Result of timing differences between taxable income reported on the Income Statement and taxable income from the company's tax return.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentLiabilities.OtherCurrentLiabilities
member.summary: OtherCurrentLiabilities includes all other liabilities that do not readily fit into the predefined categories.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.CurrentLiabilities.TotalCurrentLiabilities

member.summary: Accumulated Depreciation and Depletion is the accumulated amount of wear and tear or obsolescence charged against the fixed assets of a company. Accumulated Depletion is a reserve set up to compensate for the reduction in value of a natural resource as it is exhausted or depleted.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentAssets.NetFixedAssets
member.summary: Net Fixed Assets (Net PP&E): are those assets of a company that are of a relatively permanent nature and are not intended for resale such as property, plant and equipment. The figure is stated as cost minus accumulated depreciation & amortization.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentAssets.Intangibles
member.summary: Intangibles are those that are neither physical nor financial in nature, nevertheless, have value to the company. Intangibles are listed net of accumulated amortization.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentAssets.CostInExcess
member.summary: Intangible assets in another form, separated from the intangibles line item. Typical Accounts: Excess of cost over net tangible assets required; Intangible assets.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentAssets.NonCurrentDeferredIncomeTaxes
member.summary: A result of timing differences between taxable income reported on the Income Statement and taxable income from the company's tax return. Depending on the positioning of Deferred Income Taxes, the field may be either current (within current assets) or non-current (below total current assets). Typically a company will have 2 Deferred Income Taxes fields.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentAssets.OtherNonCurrentAssets
member.summary: are items that are not assigned to net fixed assets or intangibles.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentLiabilities.LongTermDebt
member.summary: Long-Term Debt: represents the amount of borrowings due after one year from the date of the balance sheet..

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentLiabilities.CapitalLeaseObligations
member.summary: Leases that must be reflected on a company's balance sheet.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentLiabilities.DeferredIncomeTaxLiabilities
member.summary: Deferred Income Taxes are the estimated future tax obligations which usually arise when different depreciation methods are used for financial statements and tax purposes. It is also an add-back to the Statement of Cash Flows. Deferred Income Taxes includes accumulated tax deferrals due to accelerated depreciation and investment credit.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentLiabilities.OtherNonCurrentLiabilities
member.summary: Other Non-Current Liabilities are those liabilities not assigned to long-term debt or deferred income taxes.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentLiabilities.MinorityInterestLiabilities
member.summary: represents par or stated value of the subsidiary stock not owned by the parent company plus the minority interest's equity in the surplus of the subsidiary. This item includes preferred dividend averages on the minority preferred stock (preferred shares not owned by the reporting parent company). Minority interest also refers to stockholders who own less than 50% of a subsidiary's outstanding voting common stock. The minority stockholders hold an interest in the subsidiary's net assets and share earnings with the parent company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentLiabilities.PreferredSecuritiesOfSubsidiaryTrustLiabilities
member.summary: Securities of a wholly or partially owned company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentLiabilities.PreferredEquityOutsideStockEquity
member.summary: A minority interest in the company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonCurrentLiabilities.TotalNonCurrentLiabilities
member.summary: Total Non-Current Liabilities equals long-term debt + deferred income taxes + other non-current liabilities + minority interest.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses
member.summary: Instance of NonOperatingExpenses

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses.InterestExpense
member.summary: is all fixed interest expenses net of capitalized interest. This category also includes dividends on preferred stock of unconsolidated subsidiaries, if any.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses.InterestExpenseBreakdown
member.summary: Note: Usually Financial services companies provide breakdown of some items defined in the output.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses.PreTaxIncome
member.summary: Also known as EBT, this equals EBIT minus interest expense, but before subtracting income taxes and adjusting for minority interest

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses.IncomeTaxes
member.summary: Includes any taxes or income, net of any investment tax credits. Typical Accounts: Federal income tax; State and local income tax; Income tax credit; Investment tax credits Tax benefit

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses.MinorityInterest
member.summary: Represents par or stated value of the subsidiary stock not owned by the parent company plus the minority interest's equity in the surplus of the subsidiary. This item includes preferred dividend averages on the minority preferred stock (preferred shares not owned by the reporting parent company). Minority interest also refers to stockholders who own less than 50% of a subsidiary's outstanding voting common stock. The minority stockholders hold an inerest in the subsidiary's net assets and share earnings with the parent company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses.IncomeBeforeIncomeTaxes
member.summary: Includes all the operations (continuing and discontinued) AND all the other income or charges (extraordinary, accounting changes, tax loss carryforward, and other gains and losses).

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses.NetIncomeFromContinuingOperations
member.summary: Includes income taken before the following: Preferred Dividends; Extraordinary Gains and Losses; Income from Cumulative Effects of Accounting Change; Non-Recurring Items; Income from Tax Loss Carryforward; Other Gains/Losses

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses.NetIncomeFromDiscontinuedOperations
member.summary: Income from operations sold or discontinued during the accounting period. However, it does not include extraordinary gains/losses.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonOperatingExpenses.NetIncomeFromTotalOperations
member.summary: taken from total operations (continuing + discontinued operations), after taxes and minority interest and before extraordinary gains/losses.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonRecurringEvents
member.summary: Instance of NonRecurringEvents

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonRecurringEvents.ExtraordinaryIncomeLosses
member.summary: Includes income incurred from extraordinary events and transactions that are both infrequent and unusual. Examples: 1. Act of God. 2. Property taken by a foreign country. 3. A new law/regulation. Typical Accounts: Extraordinary Items; Extraordinary Credit

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonRecurringEvents.IncomeFromCumulatedEffectOfAccountingChanges
member.summary: Gains or losses from changes in accounting for depreciation or inventory methods.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonRecurringEvents.OtherGainsAndLosses
member.summary: Includes those gains/losses incurred from an event that is both uncontrollable and often occurs in the area.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonRecurringEvents.TotalNetIncome
member.summary: Includes all the operations (continuing and discontinued) AND all the other income or charges (extraordinary, accounting changes, tax loss carryforward, and other gains and losses).

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonRecurringEvents.NormalizedIncome
member.summary: Is a calculated field: =Net Income from Continuing Operations minus Special Income / Charge.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonRecurringEvents.NetIncomeAvailableForCommon
member.summary: Equals the net income from continuing operations minus the preferred dividends paid. It represents the income available to common stockholders.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonRecurringEvents.PreferredDividends
member.summary: The total dollar amount of the current dividend requirement on issued preferred stock of the parent company. Preferred dividends are the amount required for the current year only, and not for any amount required in past years.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NonRecurringEvents.ExciseTaxes
member.summary: Excise taxes.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NormalizedRatios
member.summary: Each instance represents normalized ratios for the company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NormalizedRatios.NormalizedClosePERatio
member.summary: The price/earnings calculated using fiscal year diluted normalized net income per share.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NormalizedRatios.NormalizedHighPERatio
member.summary: The highest price a stock had (intra-day trading) for that fiscal year diluted normalized net income per share.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NormalizedRatios.NormalizedLowPERatio
member.summary: The lowest price a stock had (intra-day trading) for that fiscal year diluted normalized net income per share.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NormalizedRatios.NormalizedNetProfitMargin
member.summary: Fiscal year net income from continuing operations minus special income/charges divided by the fiscal year revenues.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NormalizedRatios.NormalizedReturnOnStockEquity
member.summary: Fiscal year earnings from continuing operations minus special income/charges divided by the common stock equity.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NormalizedRatios.NormalizedReturnOnAssets
member.summary: Fiscal year earnings from continuing operations minus special income/charges divided by the total assets.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NormalizedRatios.NormalizedReturnOnInvestedCapital
member.summary: Fiscal year earnings from continuing operations minus special income/charges divided by the invested capital (long-term debt, common stock equity, and preferred equity).

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.NormalizedRatios.NormalizedIncomePerEmployee
member.summary: Fiscal year net income from continuing operations minus special income/charges divided by the fiscal year employee number.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses
member.summary: Instance of OperatingExpenses

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.ResearchAndDevelopmentExpenses
member.summary: Research costs that may be directed toward the discovery of new facts, natural laws, or phenomena without regard to the immediate commercial application to which the results may be put or as costs directed toward more specific goals such as product improvement or the perfection and improvement of processes or techniques of production. Development costs are the costs associated with bringing the fruits of research to a commercially useful and marketable stage. Typical Accounts: Research & Development expense; Engineering & Development expense; In-process R&D.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.SellingGeneralAndAdministrativeExpenses
member.summary: Include all salaries, indirect production, marketing and general corporation expenses. Typical Accounts: include all salaries, indirect production, marketing and general corporation expenses. All provisions for doubtful accounts/losses; Commissions; Contribution to pension plans; Corporate expenses; Delivery; Distribution; Dry holes (oil and gas companies) -- if specified; Employee benefits; Employee profit sharing; Marketing Maintenance, except for utilities and railroads; Payroll; Rent; Selling, general, administrative; Storage and delivery

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.AdvertisingExpenses
member.summary: Costs associated with publicizing a good or need for sale. This category includes only Advertising, or line items beginning with advertising. Any other version of Advertising is considered Selling, General and Administrative.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.OperatingIncomeBeforeDepreciation
member.summary: Also known as EBITDA, it is the operating revenue less Adjustments to Revenue, Cost of Sales, SG&A expense, Advertising and Research & Development.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.OperatingIncome
member.summary: The difference between the Operating Revenues and Operating Expenses. A subtotal reported by the company and is not often labeled. Does not figure into the balancing of the Income Statement.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.Depreciation
member.summary: This is a non-cash charge that represents a reduction in the value of fixed assets due to wear, age, or obsolescence. This figure also includes amortization of leased property, intangibles, and goodwill, and depletion. This field is an add-back to the Statement of Cash Flows.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.DepreciationUnreconciled
member.summary: Apportionments of cost over an operational asset's useful life.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.Amortization
member.summary: The repayment of a loan by installments. Includes Amortization of any variation where Amortization is the first account listed other than Amortization of Intangibles.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.AmortizationOfIntangibles
member.summary: Systematic and rational apportionments of the acquisition cost of intangible operational assets to future periods in which the benefits contribute to revenue.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingExpenses.OperatingIncomeAfterDepreciation
member.summary: Equals EBITDA minus Depreciation and Amortization expense.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingRevenues
member.summary: Instance of OperatingRevenues

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingRevenues.TotalRevenue
member.summary: All revenues, sales and income that the company deems as a total sum of all of their income. Item is a subtotal and does not figure into the balancing of the Income Statement. Picked up exactly as the company reports it.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingRevenues.OperatingRevenue
member.summary: Includes all net sales of the corporation plus any other revenues associated with the main operations of the business (or those labeled as operating revenues). It does not include dividends, interest income or nonoperating income and is reported 'net' of any adjustments. For financial institutions: Operating Revenue = Interest Income + Non-Interest Income

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingRevenues.OperatingRevenueBreakdown
member.summary: Note: Usually Financial services companies provide breakdown of some items defined in the output.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingRevenues.AdjustmentsToRevenue
member.summary: For most companies this includes taxes other than income taxes particularly excise taxes, which the company does not actually pay, but only collects on behalf of the government (common for Tobacco, Liquor, Firearm industry) and other adjustments which have been 'netted' out of revenue. For financial companies reporting in Industrial Template, all expenses other than interest expense and income taxes are included in Adjustments to Revenue.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingRevenues.AdjustmentsToRevenueBreakdown
member.summary: for most companies this includes taxes other than income taxes particularly excise taxes, which the company does not actually pay, but only collects on behalf of the government (common for Tobacco, Liquor, Firearm industry) and other adjustments which have been 'netted' out of revenue. For financial companies reporting in Industrial Template, all expenses other than interest expense and income taxes are included in Adjustments to Revenue.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingRevenues.CostOfSales
member.summary: Includes all expenses directly associated with the production of goods or services the company sells (such as material and overhead) excluding depreciation, depletion, amortization, and SG&A. Typical Accounts: Cost of goods sold; Materials and production expenses; Gas purchased; Fuel and power purchased; Exploration and well drilling expense; Mining expenses; Oil and gas property abandonments, includes dry holes if not specified; Other operating expensesfor utilities and railroad maintenance When depreciation figures given on the Income Statement and on the Cash Flow Statement differ, compute the correct Cost of Sales figure: Cost of Sales + [(Depreciation from Income Statement) - (Depreciation from Cash Flow Statement)]

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingRevenues.CostOfSalesWithDepreciation
member.summary: All expenses directly associated with the production of goods or services the company sells. Picked up as reported on the Income Statement without adding or subtracting Depreciation, Amortization, or Amortization of Intangibles.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OperatingRevenues.GrossOperatingProfit
member.summary: As reported by the company on the face of the Income Statement. If not reported, this field is not calculated and is left as zero.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherEquityAdjustmentsBreakdown
member.summary: The amount of stockholders equity attributable to the preferred stock issued of the parent company. Note: Usually Financial services companies provide breakdown of some items defined in the output.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCashItemsBreakdown
member.summary: Breakdown of other Non-Cash items.Note: Usually Financial services companies provide breakdown of some items defined in the output.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCashItemsBreakdown.ProvisionForLoanLosses
member.summary: It is an estimate of future loan losses based on current and past figures. Usually it is an evaluation of risk, collectability, and the value of collateral in the loan portfolio.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCashItemsBreakdown.DepreciationAndAmortization
member.summary: is a non-cash charge that represents a reduction in the value of fixed assets due to wear, age or obsolescence. This figure also includes amortization of leased property, intangibles, goodwill and depletion. This field is an add-back to the Statement of Cash Flows.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCashItemsBreakdown.InvestmentSecuritiesGain
member.summary: includes income, dividends, interest and other gains received from investment securities.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCashItemsBreakdown.NetPolicyAcquisitionCosts
member.summary: a field common to insurance companies. It includes the costs associated with issuing an insurance policy.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCashItemsBreakdown.RealizedInvestmentGains
member.summary: a field common to insurance companies. It includes gains from the sale of a investment asset such as securities or real estate.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCashItemsBreakdown.ChangeInIncomeTaxes
member.summary: includes any changes in current and accrued income taxes. Does not include deferred income taxes.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCashItemsBreakdown.OtherNonCashItems
member.summary: includes all items that are not considered assets, liabilities, securities gains, taxes, insurance (policy acquisitions, realized investment gains, premiums).

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown
member.summary: Instance of OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown. Note: Usually Financial services companies provide breakdown of some items defined in the output.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.CashAndDueFromBanks
member.summary: includes any cash on hand or in banks .

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.FederalFundsSoldOrSecuritiesPurchased
member.summary: Includes any federal government securities that have been sold or purchased.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.InterestBearingDepositsAtOtherBanks
member.summary: Includes all interest earning deposits kept in other banks.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.NetInvestmentSecurities
member.summary: Includes the net of any of the securities listed below.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.Loans
member.summary: Gross Loans is a field common to banks. It is the sum of the total amount being borrowed.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.UnearnedPremiumsAssets
member.summary: It includes policy cancellations and any amounts that have been paid for insurance coverage where the time has not elapsed yet.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.AllowanceForLoansAndLeaseLosses
member.summary: Includes any unamortized interest discounts, allowances for possible losses and adjustments to historical costs.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.NetLoans
member.summary: Equals Gross Loans minus Unearned Premium plus Allowances for Loans and Lease Loss

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.PremisesAndEquipment
member.summary: Includes fixed assets such as property, plant, and equipment.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.DueFromCustomersAcceptance
member.summary: Includes any amounts due from customers.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.TradingAccountSecurities
member.summary: A field common to banks. It is basically a trust fund where the bank has full fiduciary rights over the money an investor places in the trust. The bank invests the money in securities and the client has to pay fees for this service.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.OtherReceivables
member.summary: Receivables that are not assigned to due from customers on acceptance

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.AccruedInterest
member.summary: Includes any accrued interest receivable on investments

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.DeferredAcquisitionCost
member.summary: Includes any deferred costs from policy acquisitions. It includes the costs and expenses for issuing insurance policies.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.AccruedInvestmentIncome
member.summary: Includes any accrued income from investments

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.SeparateAccountBusiness
member.summary: Includes revenue generated that is not part of typical operations.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.TimeDepositsPlaced
member.summary: includes deposits that must stay in the bank for a certain period of time before they can be collected without sustaining a penalty

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentAssetsBreakdown.OtherAssets
member.summary: Includes any items that are not assigned to categories under total money market investments in the income statement

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.NonInterestBearingDeposits
member.summary: Most deposits are interest bearing, so unless it is specifically stated "Non-Interest Bearing" nothing is entered here.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.OtherLiabilities
member.summary: includes all other liabilities not assigned to non-interest bearing deposits or interest bearing deposits.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.BankersAcceptanceOutstanding
member.summary: a short-term debt instrument issued by a firm, but payment is guaranteed by a commercial bank.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.FederalsFundsPurchasedSecuritiesSold
member.summary: include any federal government funds and securities that have been sold.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.AccruedTaxes
member.summary: can be assigned to the following accounts: Federal income tax; State and local income tax; Income tax credit; Investment tax credits; Tax benefits.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.AccruedInterestPayables
member.summary: any accrued interest that is payable.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.OtherPayables
member.summary: includes any amounts that are payable or considered current liabilities.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.CapitalLeaseObligations
member.summary: Capitalized Lease Obligations includes fixed assets (property, plant, equipment) that are leased.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.ClaimsAndClaimExpense
member.summary: a field common to insurance companies. It includes claims and claims expense against insurance policies.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.FuturePolicyBenefits
member.summary: a field common to insurance companies. It is a cumulative amount held in reserves to cover claims.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.UnearnedPremiumsLiabilities
member.summary: a field common to insurance companies. It includes policy cancellations and any amounts that have been paid for insurance coverage where the time has not elapsed yet.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.PolicyHolderFunds
member.summary: a field common to insurance companies. It is the net equity of the company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.ParticipatingPolicyholderEquity
member.summary: a field common to insurance companies. It includes any dividends, preferred or common stock that a policyholder has gained from the insurance company investing in investment securities. The policyholder cannot collect the equity until they cash in the policy.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherNonCurrentLiabilitiesBreakdown.SeparateAccountBusiness
member.summary: a liability generated that is not part of typical business operations.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios
member.summary: Each instance represents other common ratios for the company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.QuickRatio
member.summary: The fiscal year Cash and Equivalents plus Receivables divided by Current Liabilities.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.CurrentRatio
member.summary: The fiscal year Total Current Assets divided by the Total Current Liabilities.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.PayoutRatio
member.summary: Most recent 4 quarters Dividends Paid Per Share divided by the most recent 4 quarters Diluted EPS from Total Operations, expressed as a percentage. Footnotes: If EPS = 0, then "NC" will be the value; If EPS less than 0, then "NE" will be the value.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.TotalDebtToEquityRatio
member.summary: The fiscal year Short-term Debt + Long-Term debt divided by the Total Common Equity.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.LeverageRatio
member.summary: The fiscal year Total Assets divided by Total Stockholders' Equity.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.AssetTurnover
member.summary: Measures the ratio at which each dollar of assets will generate a dollar of revenue/sales. Fiscal year Revenue divided by average of the Total Assets from the latest two fiscal years.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.CashAsPercentageOfRevenue
member.summary: The fiscal year cash and cash equivalents divided by the latest fiscal year revenue, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.ReceivablesAsPercentageOfRevenue
member.summary: The fiscal year accounts receivables divided by the latest fiscal year revenue, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.SGAndAExpenseAsPercentageOfRevenue
member.summary: The fiscal year SG&A Expense divided by the fiscal year revenue, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.RAndDExpenseAsPercentageOfRevenue
member.summary: The fiscal year R&D Expense divided by the fiscal year revenue, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.RevenuePerCash
member.summary: Is equal to the fiscal year revenue divided by the fiscal year cash and equivalents.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.RevenuePerPlant
member.summary: Is equal to the fiscal year revenue divided by the fiscal year net property, plant, and equipment.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.RevenuePerCommonEquity
member.summary: Is equal to the fiscal year revenue divided by the fiscal year common stock equity.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.RevenuePerInvestedCapital
member.summary: Is equal to the fiscal year revenue divided by the fiscal year invested capital (long-term debt + preferred equity + common equity).

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.ReceivableTurnover
member.summary: The fiscal year revenue divided by average receivables from the past two fiscal year balance sheets.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.InventoryTurnover
member.summary: Measures the velocity with which merchandise move through a firm. Fiscal year Cost of Goods Sold divided by average of Inventories from the latest two fiscal years.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.ReceivablesPerDaySales
member.summary: Also called the "average collection period." It indicates the average length of time a firm must wait after making a sale before it receives payment. Fiscal year Accounts Receivable divided by Sales divided by 360.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.SalesPerReceivables
member.summary: The fiscal year revenue (sales) divided by that latest fiscal year accounts receivables.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.SalesPerInventory
member.summary: The fiscal year revenue (sales) divided by that latest fiscal year inventories.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.RevenueToAssets
member.summary: The fiscal year revenue divided by the latest fiscal year total assets.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.NumberOfDaysCostOfGoodsSoldInInventory
member.summary: average inventory from the past two annual balance sheets divided by (fiscal year cost of goods divided by 360).

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.CurrentAssetsPerShare
member.summary: The fiscal year current assets divided by the fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.TotalAssetsPerShare
member.summary: The fiscal year total assets divided by the fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.IntangiblesAsPercentageBookValue
member.summary: the fiscal year intangibles divided by the latest fiscal year common equity, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.LongTermDebtPerShare
member.summary: The fiscal year long-term debt divided by the fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.CurrentLiabilitiesPerShare
member.summary: The fiscal year current liabilities divided by the fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.CashPerShare
member.summary: Equals the fiscal year cash & equivalents divided by fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.LongTermDebtToEquityRatio
member.summary: The fiscal year Long-term debt divided by the Total Common Equity.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.LongTermDebtAsPercentageOfInvestedCapital
member.summary: the fiscal year long-term debt divided by the invested capital, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.LongTermDebtAsPercentageOfTotalLiabilities
member.summary: the fiscal year long-term debt divided by the total debt (long-term + short-term debt), expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.TotalLiabilitiesAsPercentageOfTotalAssets
member.summary: The fiscal year total debt divided by the total assets, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.WorkingCapitalAsPercentageOfEquity
member.summary: is the fiscal year working capital (current assets - current liabilities) divided by the fiscal year book value, expressed as a percentage

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.RevenuePerShare
member.summary: The fiscal year revenue divided by the latest fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.BookValuePerShare
member.summary: The fiscal year common equity (book value) divided by the fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.TangibleBookValuePerShare
member.summary: [fiscal year common equity (book value) minus intangibles] divided by the fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.PriceToRevenueRatio
member.summary: The closing price of the stock on the last trading day of the fiscal year divided by the revenue/sales per share.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.PriceToTangibleBookRatio
member.summary: The closing price of the stock of the last trading day of the fiscal year divided by fiscal year tangible book value per share. Tangible book value per share is calculated as follows: [fiscal year common equity (book value) minus intangibles] divided by the fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.WorkingCapitalAsPercentageOfPrice
member.summary: is the fiscal year working capital (current assets - current liabilities) per share divided by the latest fiscal year closing price, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.WorkingCapitalPerShare
member.summary: The fiscal year working capital (current assets - current liabilities) divided by the fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.CashFlowPerShare
member.summary: Equals [fiscal year Net Income from Total Operations minus Preferred Dividends plus Depreciation] divided by fiscal year common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.FreeCashFlowPerShare
member.summary: This is calculated on an Annual and Quarterly period, derived from the Year-to-Date Cash Flow statement. [Cash Flow from Operating Activities minus Purchase of Property Plant & Equipment minus Payment of Cash Dividends] divided by Total Shares Outstanding

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.ReturnOnStockEquity
member.summary: Fiscal year earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items) divided by the common stock equity, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.ReturnOnInvestedCapital
member.summary: Fiscal year earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items) divided by the invested capital (long-term debt, common stock equity, and preferred equity), expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.ReturnOnAssets
member.summary: Fiscal year earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items) divided by the total assets, expressed as a percentage.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.PriceCashFlowRatio
member.summary: The closing price of the stock of the last trading day of the fiscal year divided by fiscal year cash flow per share.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.OtherRatios.SalesPerEmployee
member.summary: The fiscal year revenue divided by the fiscal year employee number.

member.summary: Each instance represents report header providing details of the report from which data is provided in the result.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.ReportHeader.ReportType
member.summary: Report type to be used to fetch requested data.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.ReportHeader.ReportDate
member.summary: Filing date of the report used for requested data.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.ReportHeader.FiscalQuarter
member.summary: Fiscal quarter of the of the report used for requested data.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.ReportHeader.AuditorsName
member.summary: Name of the auditor used by the Company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.ReportHeader.AuditorsReport
member.summary: Auditor's name and opinition . This data is not avialble at this time.

member.name: T:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity
member.summary: Instance of StockHolderEquity

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.PreferredStockEquity
member.summary: The amount of stockholders equity attributable to the preferred stock issued of the parent company.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.CommonStockEquity
member.summary: the amount of shareholders equity attributable to common stock. This figure taken from the annual or quarterly reports.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.CommonPar
member.summary: Equal to the nominal or face value of a security.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.AdditionalPaidInCapital
member.summary: Capital received from investors in exchange for stock, as distinguished from capital generated from earnings or donated.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.CumulativeTranslationAdjustment
member.summary: Adjustments for foreign currencies.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.RetainedEarnings
member.summary: The portion of net income that has been retained for reinvestment in the company rather than being paid in dividends to the shareholders.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.TreasuryStock
member.summary: Treasury Stock.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.OtherEquityAdjustmentsBreakdown
member.summary: The amount of stockholders equity attributable to the preferred stock issued of the parent company. Note: Usually Financial services companies provide breakdown of some items defined in the output.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.TotalCapitalization
member.summary: Equals total equity + long-term debt.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.TotalEquity
member.summary: equals preferred stock equity + common stock equity.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.TotalLiabilitiesAndStockEquity
member.summary: the sum of the total liabilities and the shareholders equity.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.CashFlow
member.summary: equals Net Income from Total Operations minus Preferred Dividends plus Depreciation as taken from the annual report.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.WorkingCapital
member.summary: equals Current Assets - Current Liabilities.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.FreeCashFlow
member.summary: Free Cash Flow: calculated as follows on an Annual and Quarterly basis: Cash from Operations minus Purchase of Plant, Property, and Equipment minus Payment of Cash Dividends. Note: Cash Flow Statements are reported as 'Year-to-Date'.

member.name: P:Xignite.Sdk.Api.Models.XigniteFinancials.StockHoldersEquity.InvestedCapital
member.summary: Invested Capital equals Long-Term Debt + Preferred Equity + Common Equity.
